(91, 1, '2015-02-09 07:22:28', '2015-02-09 07:22:28', '<strong>Introduction:</strong>\r\n\r\nStayble therapeutics is developing a minimally invasive injection-based treatment against chronic low back pain triggered by tears in the disc caused by disc degeneration. Stayble offer a solution that actually will remove the pain for the patients without the need for surgery.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Problem</strong>\r\n\r\ncLBP is a disabling and extremely expensive condition for the healthcare sector and for society, affecting millions of patients and generating annual total costs exceeding €80 billion in the US alones<sup>1</sup>. It is well acknowledged that the cause of pain is unknown for 90-95% of all cases of cLBP, described as idiopathic low back pain. This makes cLBP very difficult to address therapeutically. However, recently it was established that a major cause of pain result from leakage of disc material through tears of the degenerating (aging) disc often referred to as discogenic pain <sup>2–4</sup>. The pro-inflammatory disc material thus comes in contact with the nerves on the outer surface of the disc, which is known to produce pain in the lower back if stimulated <sup>5,6</sup>. A disc consists of two parts; the liquid disc centre and the disc wall.\r\n\r\nToday, spinal fusion is the only available treatment for patients with discogenic pain, who do not respond to the usual conservative treatment with painkillers and physiotherapy. It is an ineffective, invasive and by many a questioned procedure with rehabilitation of up to 6 months and accompanying work absence of up to 2 years. In addition according to interviewed surgeons only 60% of the patients can expect to get better after the treatment whereas 24% remain unchanged and 16% become worse.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Our solution:</strong>\r\n\r\nStayble Therapeutics (Stayble) is developing an injection-based treatment against discogenic pain that will effectively remove the pain and the need for spinal fusion. Stayble’s treatment offers the patient a completely new way to treat its chronic low back pain and will drastically change the way surgeons treat cLBP. Stayble’s treatment will be a breakthrough with its efficacy and simplicity compare to today’s complex and ineffective treatment regimes.\r\n\r\nThe treatment is based on an existing drug substance giving Stayble access to existing safety data and the possibility to buy the substance off the shelf. This will generate a shorter time to market at a much lower risk than conventional pharmaceutical development. The injection treatment works in the way of fully transform the disc centre from being a liquid into connective tissue, as shown in the figure below. Either a spine surgeon or a radiologist will perform the treatment.\r\n\r\nThe transformation of the disc centre will remove the pain-causing component (the leakage) and in a simple, cost-saving and minimally-invasive (according to the classification of spinal interventions) way eliminate the pain for the patients. The treatment is assumed to be effective within 4 weeks, last the patient’s entire life and require no need for rehabilitation. With this treatment, Stayble is first to directly target the pain provoking mechanism behind discogenic low back pain, allowing the patient to be pain free. Stayble will be able to fulfil the need of a new take-on towards treatment of discogenic pain where there today are very few actors actually able to remove the patient’s pain, for comparison, see <em>Competition</em>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStayble’s treatment in short\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimally-invasive single injection based treatment</li>\r\n	<li>Directly targeting the pain provoking mechanism</li>\r\n	<li>Does not require the patient to stay in the hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Estimated to have low COGS</li>\r\n	<li>If the treatment fails to reduce the pain it will not block other treatment options</li>\r\n	<li>Is estimated to be efficient within 4 weeks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Pre-clinical verification of the concept</strong>\r\n\r\nStayble has successfully demonstrated that an injection of its treatment transforms the disc centre into connective tissue, as indicated by the red lines in the picture of a treated, disc below. This transformation was demonstrated in a pig model. The mechanisms and dose-response has been confirmed in vitro by adding the substance to cell lines and measuring the amount of connective tissue produced.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAdd link to one-pager', 'Technology', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-09 07:22:28', '2015-02-09 07:22:28', '', 43, 'http://localhost/phptest/stayble/43-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2015-02-18 10:32:09', '2015-02-18 10:32:09', '<p class="ingress">Stayble therapeutics is developing a minimally invasive injection-based treatment against chronic low back pain triggered by tears in the disc caused by disc degeneration. Stayble offer a solution that actually will remove the pain for the patients without the need for surgery.</p>\n[ezcol_1half]\n<h2>Market info</h2>\nStayble’s initial market will be patients that today receive a spinal fusion for their discogenic pain. This patient group consist of approximately 100 000 fusions performed yearly in the US and EU. A group of patients that Stayble will be able to charge a high price and verify its treatment procedure.\n\nIn a second phase the aim is to target the market of patients suffering from moderate discogenic pain for whom the risks and the costs associated with a spinal fusion exceeds the likely benefit. This will be a much larger patient group but where we will be harder to get initial acceptance and where the pricing will be lower.\n\n[/ezcol_1half]\n\n[ezcol_1half]\n\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-260 alignright" src="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/bubbla.png" alt="bubbla" width="200" height="213" />\n\n[/ezcol_1half]\n\n[ezcol_end_both]\n\n[ezcol_1half]\n<h2>Market penetration and estimated peak sale</h2>\nThe market penetration is estimated to start rather slow to gain acceptance of the new treatment procedure on the market. This due to that spinal surgeons are a relatively conservative group. It is, however, very well connected with a large community with will mean that once Stayble’s treatment will be accepted on the market by the main drivers we estimate a more rapid adoption.\n\nThis segment involves in the initial market focus approximately 32 000 patients (US, EU). At a sales price of €4000 this equals to a yearly income of 128MEUR just in the segment of fusions (towards degenerative disc disease) today. When the product has been accepted on the market we estimate an extensive increase in usage towards a broader indication\n\n[/ezcol_1half]\n\n[ezcol_1half]\n<h3>Estimated product price of €4000</h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3>128 MEUR in peak sales</h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h6>Great possibility to expand the market</h6>\n[/ezcol_1half]', 'Market', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '45-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-02-18 10:32:09', '2015-02-18 10:32:09', '', 45, 'http://localhost/phptest/stayble/45-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
