(111, 1, '2015-02-09 10:53:38', '2015-02-09 10:53:38', '<blockquote><strong>Stayble therapeutics is developing a minimally invasive injection-based treatment against chronic low back pain triggered by tears in the disc caused by disc degeneration. Stayble offer a solution that actually will remove the pain for the patients without the need for surgery.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h3><strong>Market</strong></h3>\r\nThe initial market for Stayble will be patients that are scheduled to undergo a spinal fusion and are suffering from discogenic pain caused by disc degeneration (often referred as degenerative disc disease) with a confirmed leakage from the disc. This patient group consist of approximately 130 000 fusions performed in the US and EU of which around 100 000 patients will be treatable with Stayble´s product. The reason for choosing this segment as a starting point is that it is a good market to verify the concept and a segment where we will be able to charge a high product price, see <i>Health economic.</i>\r\n\r\nIn a second phase the aim is to target the market of patients suffering from moderate discogenic pain for whom the risks and the costs associated with a spinal fusion exceeds the likely benefit. This will be a much larger patient group but where we will be harder to get initial acceptance and where the pricing will be lower.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Current treatments</strong></h3>\r\nThere is currently no available treatment that targets the pain-provoking component of discogenic pain as Stayble’s does. Competition, however, relates to more advanced fusion devices and new types of implants, which only incrementally improve the outcome for the patient.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Pricing</strong></h3>\r\nA pricing comparison has been made comparing with the cost for the minimally invasive treatments identified in Competition above. The cost for a steroid injection is approximately €100 for the product and around € 500 for the actual procedure, yielding a total cost of €600 per treatment. Patients undergo this type of treatment 3 times per year (every year) at a cost of €1800. Thermal procedures are more expensive with a cost for the disposable needle of around €800 and a procedure cost of €6000. It is important to remember that the compared treatments (steroids and thermal energy) are not considered to be a cure and needs to be repeated to take away the pain. The only cure is the fusion, at a cost of approximately €22 000.\r\n\r\nStayble´s procedure cost is estimated to around €1300 according to our health economic assessment, see below. The pricing for the product is estimated to between €3-5000, yielding a lower total cost than thermal energy and a similar cost to three year treatment with steroids but actually removing the pain.\r\n\r\n100 000 patients are being fused for this specific problem. All can be treated by Stayble.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Market penetration and estimated peak sale</strong></h3>\r\nThe market penetration is estimated to start rather slow to gain acceptance of the new treatment procedure on the market. This due to that spinal surgeons are a relatively conservative group. It is, however, very well connected with a large community with will mean that once Stayble’s treatment will be accepted on the market by the main drivers we estimate a more rapid adoption.\r\n\r\nStayble estimate that after 6 years on the market have approximately 33 % of the market share. This segment involves in the initial market focus approximately 32 000 patients (US, EU).\r\n\r\nAt a sales price of €4000 this equals to a yearly income of 128MEURO just in the segment of fusions (towards degenerative disc disease) today. When the product has been accepted on the market we estimate an extensive increase in usage towards a broader indication\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Intellectual Property</strong></h3>\r\nStayble has in March 20th 2014 applied for a patent for the use of our substance (in the US a use patent and in the EU a pharmaceutical product patent according to the EPO legislation) for the treatment of intervertebral discs (discs in the spine).\r\n\r\nPrior to the application, a detailed analysis of the freedom to operate (FTO) was performed in collaboration with Awapatent. The result from this study is that the invention is patentable and that there is freedom to operate. This was further evaluated by Anders Bergman, Profora who performed a second opinion of the work done by Awapatent with the same conclusion that the invention is patentable, has an inventive step and freedom to operate.\r\n<h3><strong>Based on an existing substance</strong></h3>\r\nOne important success factor relating to the development of Stayble’s treatment is that it is based on an existing drug substance giving us access to available data relating to toxicology of the substance, previous data relating to adverse effects and methods of analysing levels in human tissue and blood. This in combination leads to a decrease development time, risk and cost throughout the development.\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc409626069"></a><strong>Financing</strong></h3>\r\nStayble is currently financed by a Vinnova (Sweden''s innovation agency<em>)</em> grant of € 215 000 awarded in August 2014. The funds are distributed over a period of 18 months and provide a cornerstone in the funding of Stayble until January 2016. In addition Stayble was awarded a research grant of €50 000 in September 2014.\r\n<pre>The following actors have previously funded Stayble:</pre>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Encubator AB</li>\r\n	<li>Vinnova</li>\r\n	<li>Almi</li>\r\n	<li>Innovationskontor Väst</li>\r\n	<li>FRF-stiftelsen</li>\r\n	<li>GU Holding</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo be able to accelerate the development towards an application for clinical trials Stayble is currently searching for further financing, initially 0,5MEUR. The total cost for development until PoC in humans is estimated to 2,9 MEUR divided into three different financing rounds according to the graphics below. For a more detailed description see coming headlines.\r\n\r\nThe calculations relating to the development cost has been benchmarked with similar biotech start-ups that has gone through a similar development process until PoC in humans.\r\n\r\nAdd link to one-pager\r\n\r\nBusiness plan upon request</blockquote>', 'Investors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '45-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-09 10:53:38', '2015-02-09 10:53:38', '', 45, 'http://localhost/phptest/stayble/45-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
