hrough with its efficacy and simplicity compare to today’s complex and ineffective treatment regimes.\r\n\r\nThe treatment is based on an existing drug substance giving Stayble access to existing safety data and the possibility to buy the substance off the shelf. This will generate a shorter time to market at a much lower risk than conventional pharmaceutical development.\r\n\r\nThe injection treatment works in the way of fully transform the disc centre from being a liquid into connective tissue, as shown in the figure below. Either a spine surgeon or a radiologist will perform the treatment.\r\n\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\nThe transformation of the disc centre will remove the pain-causing component (the leakage) and in a simple, cost-saving and minimally-invasive (according to the classification of spinal interventions) way eliminate the pain for the patients. The treatment is assumed to be effective within 4 weeks, last the patient’s entire life and require no need for rehabilitation.\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\nWith this treatment, Stayble is first to directly target the pain provoking mechanism behind discogenic low back pain, allowing the patient to be pain free. Stayble will be able to fulfil the need of a new take-on towards treatment of discogenic pain where there today are very few actors actually able to remove the patient’s pain, for comparison, see Competition.\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n[ezcol_end_both]\r\n<h2>Stayble’s treatment in short</h2>\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimally-invasive single injection based treatment</li>\r\n	<li>Directly targeting the pain provoking mechanism</li>\r\n	<li>Does not require the patient to stay in the hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Estimated to have low COGS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/disk.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-246" src="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/disk.png" alt="disk" width="300" height="196" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n[ezcol_end_both]\r\n\r\nIf the treatment fails to reduce the pain it will not block other treatment options\r\n\r\nIs estimated to be efficient within 4 weeks\r\n<h2>Pre-clinical verification of the concept</h2>\r\nStayble has successfully demonstrated that an injection of its treatment transforms the disc centre into connective tissue, as indicated by the red lines in the picture of a treated, disc below. This transformation was demonstrated in a pig model. The mechanisms and dose-response has been confirmed in vitro by adding the substance to cell lines and measuring the amount of connective tissue produced.', 'Technology', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-18 09:23:01', '2015-02-18 09:23:01', '', 43, 'http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/43-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(275, 1, '2015-02-18 09:26:47', '2015-02-18 09:26:47', '<p class="ingress">Stayble is developing a minimally invasive injection-based treatment against chronic low back pain. Stayble offer a solution that actually will remove the pain for the patients without the need for surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The Problem</h2>\r\nStayble focuses on patients suffering from cLBP where the pain is caused by a leakage of inflammatory substances from the disc centre. The leakage occurs through tears in the disc wall caused by an aging process of the disc.\r\n\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\nToday spinal fusion is the only treatment for patients with cLBP who do not respond to the usual conservative treatment of analgesics and physiotherapy.\r\n\r\nThe direct cost of a spinal fusion is € 22 000 and is followed by up to 6 months of rehabilitation with accompanying work absence of up to two years. In addition only 60% of the treated patients will actually become better from the treatment while 40 % remain unchanged or become worse\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/bubbla.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-260" src="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/bubbla.png" alt="bubbla" width="200" height="213" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n<h2>STAYBLES UNIQUE TREATMENT</h2>\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/disk.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-246" src="http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/disk.png" alt="disk" width="300" height="196" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\n[ezcol_1half]\r\n\r\nStayble is developing an injection-based treatment against discogenic pain that will effectively remove the pain and the need for spinal fusion. Stayble’s treatment offers the patient a completely new way to treat its chronic low back pain and will drastically change the way surgeons treat cLBP.\r\n\r\nThe injection treatment works in the way of transforming the disc centre from being a liquid into solid state. The transformation of the disc will remove the pain-causing component (the leakage) and in a simple, cost-saving and minimally-invasive way eliminate the pain for the patients.\r\n\r\nThe treatment is assumed to be effective within 4 weeks, last the patient’s entire life and require no need for rehabilitation\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_1half]', 'Technology', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-18 09:26:47', '2015-02-18 09:26:47', '', 43, 'http://localhost/phptest/stayble-old/43-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
